ParallelChunk.en:
- (LT) I have a question for Mrs Lehtomäki concerning the future; 
          while
         having 21 official languages in the European Union does, of course, reflect our precious national diversity, it is, on the other hand, becoming costly and increasingly complex.

I can see that you are trying to have confidence-building measures between Europe and Iran, to try to better relations between the two of them and act as honest broker in this serious situation; 
          but
         the idea of sanctions does not really work.

